It is noteworthy to emphasize that we also determined2 the presence of C1 PrPSc in subjects with variant Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (a condition characterized by florid PrP amyloid plaques) as well as in the newly identified bovine amyloidotic spongiform encephalopathy (BASE) (3) but not in amyloid-free typical bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE).
